Chain Saw 37 each
Shipped on S.S. Kyska, B/L No. L/ .- 6.
Date of arrival Keelung: October 14, 1961. B/L sent to BES by CUS/./3D on October 23, 1961.
These items were selected by Mr. J.B. Carter/ID during his return trip from home leave. No specific enduser. Some allocated to agencies who intimated interest.
Allocated to date: THB 2 each, BES 5 each, KLHB 2 each and TIC 4 each. CUSA advise the balance (24 each) will be put up for auction on Feb. 28, 1962.
7. PO No. 60.305 /GSA PO No. 1FU-186/ICA \ PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00200
Tank, Bolted Steel 30 each
Shipped on S.S. Pres. Garfield, B/L No. 2. Date of arrival Keelung: November 30, 1961.
B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on December 6, 1961. On Jan. 15, 1962 BES advised CUS//2D these items in their yard. On Jan. 25, 1962 CUS/./2D instructed the recipient to take delivery from the BES yard.
These items were procured for TIC recommended by CUSA/JGWhite in CUSA Memo #C2-61-1649 dated May 17, 1961.
These items are stored along the road side cutside of the BES yard.
8. B60-041/GSA PO No. 3UPU-335/IC/. PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00335
Planer, OS HY, S/N 063624 1 each
Shipped on S.S. Pioneer Ming, B/L No. 8. Date of arrival Keelung: Jan. 14, 1962. B/L sent to BES by CUSA/3D on Jan. 22, 1962. Arrived BES on 2/13/62, CUSA advised on 2/15/62 On Feb. 24, 1962 CUSA advised JGWhite to check allocation.
This item was procured for KaHB recommended by CUSA/JGWhite in CUSA Memo #C2-61-2768 dated August 16, 1961.
9. B60-037/GSA PO No. 3UPU-335/ICA. PIO/C 484-99-471-0-00335
Boring Machine, S/N 41312 1 each
Shipping and arrival status is same as 8.
This item was procured for PWB recommended by CUSA/JGWhite in CUS/. Memo #C2-61-2719 dated August 11, 1961.
